      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIU, the shorter the prefix, the more restricted its ACLs are. E.g. only administrators group owns root. The longer the prefix, the broader group can own it.\n\ni find the following a bit strange:\n\nGiven a random user U\n- if U doesn\u0027t own any prefixes, U can\u0027t see metadata of any prefix\n- if admins give U permissions for prefix a/b/c/d/e/f, which is super specific and it is OK for U to own it, suddenly U can see metadata of all prefixes of a/b/c/d/e/f. This is somewhat backwards to how inheritance works in other places. Normally, if you own a prefix, you can see its descendants, NOT ancestors.\n\nWhat do you think about this?\ndid you consider to maybe return metadata only of prefixes that the requester owns?\n\non the other hand, I admit that U may want to know how can fetch their packages.\n\nif you knew all this already, maybe document it somewhere",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 80,
        "endChar": 4
      },
